1) Injection (trevor) [COMPLETE]
  o Place code in search/add functions to prevent injection. 
2) Broken Authentication
  o Set "secure" and "HttpOnly" flags for session cookies.
  o send CSRF(Cross-Site Requset Forgery) token with forms.
3) Sensitive data exposure
  o use strong ciphers and hashes
  o maintain strong encrypted communications between web and database servers
4) XML External Entities (XXE)
5) Broken Access control
6) Security misconfigurations
  o disable allow_url_fopen and allow_url_include in php.ini.
7) Cross-Site Scripting (XSS)
8) Insecure Deserialization
9) Using Components with known vulnerabilities
10) Insufficient logging and monitoring (trevor)[COMPLETE]
  o logged all errors to php.ini file. 
  o All php/db errors produce just a generic error message to the user. 



2018 owasp top 10 cheat sheet
